  "description": {
   "en": "A small shadow running around the battlefield is a \"soldier.\" He was given a military uniform and a steel helmet, and went left and right, passing through a hail of bullets to accomplish his mission! It's both sad and strong... This is the origin of Masahiro Nikaido's works, a fantastic first book that combines humor and pathos. Shotaro Ishinomori says, \"Even when the author was a magazine editor, he drew non-stop while waiting for manuscripts...The longer he waited for manuscripts, the more he enjoyed it.''He is probably the only editor in the world who said, \"The longer he waited for manuscripts, the more he enjoyed it.'' Wasn't it?\" A world of wild images condensed into one frame to two pages per work. Please enjoy a number of fantastic short nonsense."
